<h1>Problem 1: Requirements Elicitation & Prioritization in a College Attendance System</h1>

<div class="section">

<h2>Scenario</h2>

<p>
You are working as a <b>Business Analyst</b> for a College Attendance
Management System. Different stakeholders have different expectations:
</p>

<ul>
<li><b>Students</b> want a mobile app to check attendance.</li>
<li><b>Teachers</b> want biometric attendance to avoid proxy attendance.</li>
<li><b>Management</b> wants the project to be low-cost and completed quickly.</li>
</ul>

<p>
As a Business Analyst, your responsibility is to gather requirements,
prioritize them, classify features, and resolve stakeholder conflicts.
</p>

</div>

<div class="section">

<h2>1. Well-Defined Requirements</h2>

<ul>
<li>Students should be able to view attendance through a mobile application.</li>

<li>Teachers should record attendance using biometric authentication.</li>

<li>Management should receive monthly attendance reports.</li>

<li>The system should be developed within budget and completed on time.</li>

</ul>

</div>

<div class="section">

<h2>2. MoSCoW Prioritization</h2>

<table>

<tr>
<th>Priority</th>
<th>Requirement</th>
</tr>

<tr class="must">
<td>Must Have</td>
<td>Biometric Attendance System</td>
</tr>

<tr class="must">
<td>Must Have</td>
<td>Attendance Report Generation</td>
</tr>

<tr class="should">
<td>Should Have</td>
<td>Student Mobile App</td>
</tr>

<tr class="could">
<td>Could Have</td>
<td>Attendance Notifications</td>
</tr>

<tr class="wont">
<td>Won't Have (Now)</td>
<td>AI-Based Attendance Prediction</td>
</tr>

</table>

</div>

