</tr>

</table>

</div>

<div class="section">

<h2>4. Stakeholder Conflict</h2>

<h3>Conflict</h3>

<p>
Teachers insist on biometric attendance because it improves accuracy
and prevents proxy attendance. However, management wants a low-cost
solution that can be delivered quickly. Installing biometric devices
increases both cost and development time.
</p>

<h3>Resolution Plan</h3>

<ul>

<li>Conduct meetings with all stakeholders.</li>

<li>Explain the advantages and disadvantages of biometric integration.</li>

<li>Prioritize essential features for the first release.</li>

<li>Implement biometric attendance in the next phase if budget is limited.</li>

<li>Obtain approval from management and teachers before implementation.</li>

</ul>

</div>

<div class="section">

<h2>Reasoning</h2>

<p>
This problem demonstrates the importance of Requirements Engineering.
A Business Analyst collects requirements from stakeholders, prioritizes
them using the MoSCoW technique, classifies features with the Kano Model,
and resolves conflicts to ensure successful software development within
the available budget and timeline.
</p>

